label.value: Golgi Tendon Organ

value.value: The Golgi Tendon Organ is located within the tendons found on each end of a muscle. It responds to increased muscle tension or contraction as exerted on the tendon, by inhibiting further muscle contraction, which protects against muscle damage. The proprioceptive sensory neuron of a Golgi tendon organ, projects to the motor neurons located within the ventral horn of the spinal cord, where the inhibition occurs. Unlike the muscle spindle, Golgi tendon organs do not indicate muscle length, but rather muscle tension.

label.value: Cordonnier Infectious Complications Grading Scale

value.value: A three-level prognostic grading system that describes the severity of infectious complications occurring in allogeneic stem cell transplant (SCT) recipients.

label.value: Cordonnier Bacterial Complication

value.value: Any bacterially-focused infection complications occurring in allogeneic stem cell transplant recipients.

label.value: Cordonnier Fungal Complication

value.value: Any fungally-focused infection complications occurring in allogeneic stem cell transplant recipients.
A chromosome band present on 5q

label.value: Cordonnier Viral Complication

value.value: Any virally-focused infection complications occurring in allogeneic stem cell transplant recipients.

label.value: Cordonnier Parasitic Complication

value.value: Any parasite-focused infection complications occurring in allogeneic stem cell transplant recipients.

label.value: Cordonnier Nonmicrobially-Defined Infection

value.value: Any nonmicrobally-defined infection complications occurring in allogeneic stem cell transplant recipients.

label.value: Cordonnier Grade 1 Bacterial Complication, Outpatient Treatment Bacterial Focus

value.value: Any bacterially-focused infection treated as an outpatient (e.g., urinary tract infection, angina), excluding any form of bronchopneumonia.

label.value: Cordonnier Grade 2 Bacterial Complication, Bacteremia without Severe Sepsis

value.value: Any bacteremia without severe sepsis.

label.value: Cordonnier Grade 2 Bacterial Complication Requiring Inpatient Management

value.value: Any bacterially-focused infection requiring treated as an inpatient.

label.value: Cordonnier Grade 3 Bacterial Complication, Bacteremia with Severe Sepsis

value.value: Any bacteremia with severe sepsis.
